						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In Tamiḻ-Brāhmi characters. (2nd cent. B.C.)</hi></p>						

						<p>This is the second segment of the long inscription. Mentions that Ataṉ Ataṉ, the son of Kaṇaka Ataṉ as the second donor of the drip ledge of the rock shelter. At the end of the name is a crab like symbol similar to the one found in the previous inscription.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">ETE.</hi> (2014)., No. 40, p. 435.</p>						

